icle id="node-260521" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/rapeseed-oil"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/rapeseed-resized.jpg?itok=OoAhLd59" width="100" height="100" alt="Rapeseed oil" title="Rapeseed oil" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/rapeseed-oil">Rapeseed oil</a></h2><p>If you want a light alternative to other cooking oils, rapeseed is a great choice and hasâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 leeks, finely sliced">2 <a href="/glossary/leek" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">leeks</a>, finely sliced<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-252091" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/leek"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/leek.jpg?itok=hwQbd109" width="100" height="100" alt="Leeks" title="Like garlic and onion, leeks are a member of the allium family, but have their own distinct flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/leek">Leek</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">lee-k</span><p>Like garlic and onion, leeks are a member of the allium family, but have their own distinctâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 large courgette, finely diced">1 large <a href="/glossary/courgette" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">courgette</a>, finely diced<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-252031" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/courgette"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/courgette_1.jpg?itok=x26c5C0P" width="100" height="100" alt="Courgette" title="The courgette is a variety of cucurtbit, which means it&#039;s from the same family as cucumber, squash and melon" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/courgette">Courgette</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">corr-zjet</span><p>The courgette is a variety of cucurtbit, which means it's from the same family as cucumber,â€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1l boiling vegetable stock(made from scratch or with reduced-salt bouillon)">1l boiling vegetable stock (made from scratch or with reduced-salt bouillon)</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="400g can cannellini or haricot beans, drained">400g can cannellini or haricot beans, drained</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="200g green beans, chopped">200g green beans, chopped</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="3 tomatoes, chopped">3 <a href="/glossary/tomato" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">tomatoes</a>, chopped<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-254111" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/tomato"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/tomatoes.jpg?itok=_COaG0G4" width="100" height="100" alt="Tomato" title="Tomatoes are in fact a fruit, but their affinity for other savoury ingredients means that they are usually classed as a vegetable" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/tomato">Tomato</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">toe-mart-oh</span><p>A member of the nightshade family (along with aubergines, peppers and chillies), tomatoes are inâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="3 garlic cloves, finely chopped">3 garlic cloves, finely chopped</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="small pack basil">small pack <a href="/glossary/basil" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">basil</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-259946" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/basil"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/basil.jpg?itok=qx1xr6st" width="100" height="100" alt="Basil" title="The herb basil has a sweet, strong aroma and flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/basil">Basil</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ba-zil</span><p>Most closely associated with Mediterranean cooking but also very prevalent in Asian food, theâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="40g freshly grated parmesan">40g freshly grated <a href="/glossary/parmesan" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--6 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">parmesan</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--6"><article id="node-259696" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/parmesan"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/parmesan.jpg?itok=Z34jTwkR" width="100" height="100" alt="Parmesan" title="Parmesan is a straw-coloured hard cheese with a natural yellow rind and rich, fruity flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/parmesan">Parmesan</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">parm-ee-zan</span><p>Parmesan is a straw-coloured hard cheese with a natural yellow rind and rich, fruity flavour. Itâ€¦</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat the oil in a large pan and fry the leeks and courgette for 5 mins to soften. Pour in the stock, add three-quarters of the haricot beans with the green beans, half the tomatoes, and simmer for 5-8 mins until the vegetables are tender.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Meanwhile, blitz the remaining beans and tomatoes, the garlic and basil in a food processor (or in a bowl with a stick blender) until smooth, then stir in the Parmesan. Stir the sauce into the soup, cook for 1 min, then ladle half into bowls or pour into a flask for a packed lunch. Chill the remainder. Will keep for a couple of days.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1433113200" class="text-style-alt">June 2015</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div><div class="recipe__tips"><div class="field field-name-field-bbcgf-tips field-type-entityreference field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><div class="view view-recipe-views view-id-recipe_views view-display-id-tips view-dom-id-504604dba3853d99b8e19a5c57f728b7"><div class="view-content"><div class="carousel-tips__wrapper carousel"><div class="flexslider carousel-tips__elements" data-type="carousel-tips"><ul class="slides carousel-tips__slides"><li class="carousel-tips__single-slide "><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-content"><h3>Recipe Tip</h3><h4><span class="field-content">Garlic&#039;s health benefits</span></h4><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-body show-more__content">Chopping, grating or crushing garlic activates the compound allicin, thought to have a wide range of health benefits.</div></div></li><li class="carousel-tips__single-slide "><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-content"><h3>Recipe Tip</h3><h4><span class="field-content">Portion size</span></h4><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-body show-more__content">This recipe will make enough for two days - simply keep the leftovers in the fridge.</div></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content